# Borderlands SHiFT Code Aggregator - Environment Variables

# ===========================================
# Twitter API (GitHub Actions)
# ===========================================
# Twitter fetching is handled by GitHub Actions, not the browser.
# Add TWITTER_BEARER_TOKEN as a GitHub repository secret, NOT here.
#
# To set up:
# 1. Go to your GitHub repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# 2. Click "New repository secret"
# 3. Name: TWITTER_BEARER_TOKEN
# 4. Value: Your Twitter API Bearer Token
#
# The workflow runs daily and commits new codes automatically.

# ===========================================
# Local Testing (Optional)
# ===========================================
# Only needed if you want to run the fetch script locally:
# TWITTER_BEARER_TOKEN=your_bearer_token_here

# ===========================================
# Remote Data Source (Optional)
# ===========================================
# URL to fetch SHiFT codes from a remote JSON endpoint
# Use this for centralized data updates without redeploying
VITE_DATA_SOURCE_URL=
